column6: SQUARE 1: HARD MODE: A book or series that received ten votes or less.
column9: SQUARE 2: HARD MODE: Not written by Jeff VanderMeer or China Miéville.
column12: SQUARE 3: HARD MODE: Three or more authors.
column15: SQUARE 4: HARD MODE: Not based in Britain or Ireland.
column18: SQUARE 5: HARD MODE: Characters are not originally from Earth. It is acceptable for the characters to be descendants of Earthlings as long as they are not themselves from Earth.
column21: SQUARE 6: HARD MODE: Not on r/Fantasy’s Favorite Standalones List.
column24: SQUARE 7: HARD MODE: A YA book with an anti-hero.
column27: SQUARE 8: HARD MODE: Must read a current selection of either a book club or readalong and participate in the discussion.
column30: SQUARE 9: HARD MODE: Weapon has a unique name. Examples: Excalibur from Arthurian legend, Dragnipur in Malazan, Sting in Lord of the Rings, etc.
column33: SQUARE 10: HARD MODE: Revolution/Rebellion is the main focus of the plot.
column36: SQUARE 11: HARD MODE: The title has the character’s first and last name. Example: The First Fifteen Lives of Harry August.
column39: SQUARE 12: HARD MODE: Initials are a pseudonym and not from the author’s actual name. Examples: T. Kingfisher or K. J. Parker. ADDENDUM: Please do not go snooping to see if a name fits. If it isn't clear based on an author's webpage or social media, assume that it is their real name.
column42: SQUARE 13: HARD MODE: It's also a debut novel--as in it's the author's first published novel.
column45: SQUARE 14: HARD MODE: Book has an LGBTQ+ POV character.
column48: SQUARE 15: HARD MODE: Author is of African heritage.
column51: SQUARE 16: HARD MODE: Non-humanoid protagonist. No elves, angels, dwarves, hobbits, or humanoid aliens.
column54: SQUARE 17: HARD MODE: No time travel. Book involves something off about time that’s not necessarily time travel. Example: In The Chronicles of Narnia, time moves at a different speed in Narnia than in the real world.
column55: SQUARE 18: TITLE OF COLLECTION/ANTHOLOGY (go to 18A if you did 5 short stories)
column56: SQUARE 18: AUTHOR/EDITOR (go to 18A if you did 5 short stories)
column57: SQUARE 18: HARD MODE: Read an entire SFF anthology or collection.
column58: SQUARE 18A: Title of Short Story #1 (Do not fill out if you read all of a collection/anthology)
column60: SQUARE 18B: Title of Short Story #2 (Do not fill out if you read all of a collection/anthology)
column62: SQUARE 18C: Title of Short Story #3 (Do not fill out if you read all of a collection/anthology)
column64: SQUARE 18D: Title of Short Story #4 (Do not fill out if you read all of a collection/anthology)
column66: SQUARE 18E: Title of Short Story #5 (Do not fill out if you read all of a collection/anthology)
column70: SQUARE 19: HARD MODE: Not The Stormlight Archive or any books in the linked list.
column73: SQUARE 20: HARD MODE: Self-published and has fewer than 100 ratings on Goodreads, OR an indie publisher that has done an AMA with r/Fantasy.
column76: SQUARE 21: HARD MODE: Neither Hugo-nominated nor Nebula-nominate.
column79: SQUARE 22: HARD MODE: A book written by an Indigenous author.
column82: SQUARE 23: HARD MODE: Most prominent shifter is not a wolf/dog shifter. For instance, werewolves can exist but can’t be the most notable shifter characters/main characters.
column85: SQUARE 24: HARD MODE: Title is three words or more.
column88: SQUARE 25: HARD MODE: Features at least three generations in a single family.
